  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a four-byte ASCII tag used to identify font tables and OpenType features.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` wraps a `uint` that encodes four ASCII characters as a big-endian byte sequence (e.g., `'w','g','h','t'` = `0x77676874`). It is used to identify variation axes, font tables, and OpenType feature tags.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from four characters
var wght = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');

// Round-trip through string
Console.WriteLine(wght.ToString()); // "wght"

// Implicit conversion to/from uint
uint raw = wght;
SKFourByteTag tag = raw;
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
